939. Health Econ. 2006 Oct;15(10):1149-54. doi: 10.1002/hec.1122.

A theoretical framework for TTO valuations of health.

Buckingham K(1), Devlin N.

Author information:
(1)Department of Preventive and Social Medicine, Otago University, New Zealand.

This paper proposes a theoretical framework, drawing on Hicks utility theory, 
for the Time Trade-off (TTO) method conventionally used to value health states. 
We briefly describe that theory and posit four distinctive TTO valuation 
approaches suggested by it: each of compensating variation and equivalent 
variation for both gains and losses in health, with valuation of health states 
in each case derived from trade-offs between health and length of life. Recent 
developments and research on TTO valuation are placed in the context of this 
framework.

